  "summary": "Import-time C2 backdoor with dual JS and native shell-command channel",
  "details": "On require(), index.js hex-decodes the URL http://152.53.120.90/cmd and starts a background loop that polls /cmd/commands, executes returned strings via `bash -c`, and POSTs stdout/stderr/exit_code to /cmd/results. The bundled native addon sysmon.cc, invoked from index.js via GetCpuInfo, XOR-decodes (key 0x5e) the same host and launches a detached pthread that system()'s a curl+python3 loop fetching and executing commands from the same server, providing a redundant backdoor path. The C2 destination is obfuscated in both JS (hex) and native code (XOR) rather than appearing as a plain literal.",
